# Format-agnostic documentation

**Critical rule.** When editing related files, if you notice existing code or docs that violate this rule — even outside your current task — **flag it to the user as a high concern** before or alongside your main work. Do not silently ignore, copy the pattern, or defer without mention.

The **library** and feature docs describe **our** product model — not any single vendor CPS. OpenGD77 is **one** import/export format among several (DM32, qDMR, CHIRP, native YAML).

## Internal model docs (`docs/features/`)

- Describe library entities, format builds, traits, and internal UUID relationships.
- Point wire-format mapping to `docs/reference/formats/<format>/` and import/export feature docs — not OpenGD77 alone.
- Radio caps and truncation belong in format/reference docs and export adapters, not library-model docs.

## Unacceptable

- "Wire-format column detail lives in the [OpenGD77 reference](…)" — implies OpenGD77 is the only external model.
- "Wire-column mappings for every field above live in the [OpenGD77 reference](…)" — same.
- "Import an OpenGD77 export on the home page" as the **only** way to get test data — implies OpenGD77 is the only format.
- Describing **library** organisation using one format's CSV layout (e.g. zones because OpenGD77 has `Zones.csv`).

## Acceptable

- "CSVs are mapped by the import/export layer (e.g. OpenGD77 → library types)."
- "Import any supported CPS export (OpenGD77, DM32, CHIRP, …) or start a blank project."
- "See [OpenGD77 reference](../../docs/reference/formats/opengd77/README.md) for OpenGD77 column mapping" — scoped to that format.
- "Build UI composes from capability traits; wire adapters map trait layout per format."

## Quick check

Before linking to `docs/reference/formats/opengd77/`, ask: is this sentence about **OpenGD77 specifically**, or about **all** external formats? If the latter, link import/export docs or list formats explicitly.
